---
import SiteLayout from "../components/SiteLayout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Outpost — CLI workspace manager for multi-repo tickets"
  description="Create deterministic Git worktree layouts for tickets that span multiple repositories. One command to branch, worktree, and orient coding agents across your repos."
>
  <article class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Outpost</h1>
      <p>
        CLI workspace manager for multi-repository tickets. Create branches,
        worktrees, and agent orientation files across your repos with a single
        command.
      </p>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow" style="margin: 0 0 var(--space-2xs);">Install</p>
        <div class="code-block-shell">
          <code class="command-code" translate="no"
            >npm install -g @abijith-suresh/outpost</code
          >
          <button
            type="button"
            class="copy-button"
            aria-label="Copy install command to clipboard"
            data-copy-command="npm install -g @abijith-suresh/outpost"
          >
            <svg
              data-copy-icon
              width="16"
              height="16"
              viewBox="0 0 16 16"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.5"
            >
              <rect x="5.5" y="5.5" width="8" height="8" rx="1"></rect>
              <path d="M3 10.5V3a1 1 0 0 1 1-1h7.5"></path>
            </svg>
            <svg
              data-check-icon
              class="hidden"
              width="16"
              height="16"
              viewBox="0 0 16 16"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2"
            >
              <path d="M3 8l3.5 3.5L13 4"></path>
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
        <p style="margin: var(--space-2xs) 0 0; font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted);">
          Requires Node.js &ge; 22.14.0 and Git on PATH.
        </p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section aria-labelledby="what-is" class="prose">
      <h2 id="what-is">What it does</h2>
      <p>
        A ticket like <code translate="no">PROJ-123</code> often spans a backend
        repo, a frontend repo, and a shared library. Outpost creates matching
        branches and worktrees across all of them, then writes an orientation
        file that tells you and your coding agent exactly where everything lives.
      </p>
      <div class="terminal-block" aria-label="Abbreviated example of outpost create output">
        <pre><span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost create --ticket PROJ-123 --type feat --repo api --repo web --repo shared

<span class="terminal-output">outpost create
ticket: PROJ-123
branch: feat/PROJ-123
workspace directory: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123
worktrees: 3

- api (id: api)
  path: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123/api
  branch: feat/PROJ-123
  base: main
- web (id: web)
  path: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123/web
  branch: feat/PROJ-123
  base: main
- shared (id: shared)
  path: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123/shared
  branch: feat/PROJ-123
  base: main</span></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="safety" class="prose">
      <h2 id="safety">Safety guarantees</h2>
      <p>
        Outpost is pre-v1 and focused on local workspace management. Every
        mutation is guarded.
      </p>
      <ul class="state-list">
        <li>
          <span class="state-dot ready" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>Dirty worktree protection.</strong> Workspace removal checks <code translate="no">git status --porcelain</code> and refuses worktrees with uncommitted changes.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="state-dot ready" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>Ownership verification.</strong> Worktrees must point to the expected bare repositories. Outpost never adopts state it cannot prove it owns.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="state-dot ready" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>Ticket locks.</strong> Concurrent operations on the same ticket are serialized with file locks.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="state-dot ready" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>Rollback.</strong> If creation fails partway through, branches, worktrees, and generated files are rolled back.</span>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="state-dot ready" aria-hidden="true"></span>
          <span><strong>Partial success reporting.</strong> Batch operations like <code translate="no">repo fetch</code> report individual results rather than hiding failures.</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="agent-orientation" class="prose">
      <h2 id="agent-orientation">Agent orientation</h2>
      <p>
        Every workspace includes an <code translate="no">AGENTS.md</code> that
        coding agents can read to understand the workspace layout, expected
        branches, and repository structure. Outpost verifies file ownership on
        removal to protect user edits.
      </p>
      <div class="terminal-block" aria-label="Abbreviated example of generated AGENTS.md content">
        <pre><span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>cat ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123/AGENTS.md

<span class="terminal-output"># Outpost Workspace

This directory coordinates one ticket workspace. It is not a Git repository.

## Working Rules

- Each listed child directory is an independent Git worktree.
- Run Git, build, test, and commit commands inside the relevant worktree.

## Workspace

```
    ticket: "PROJ-123"
    expectedBranch: "feat/PROJ-123"
```

### Repository 1

```
    name: "api"
    id: "api"
    worktree: "./api"
    expectedBranch: "feat/PROJ-123"
    baseBranch: "main"
```</span></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="workflow" class="prose">
      <h2 id="workflow">Workflow</h2>
      <div class="terminal-block">
        <pre><span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost init
<span class="terminal-output">outpost init
outpost home: ~/.outpost
repos root: ~/.outpost/repos
worktrees root: ~/.outpost/worktrees</span>

<span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost repo add ./my-project
<span class="terminal-output">outpost repo add
source repo path: ./my-project
remote name: origin
remote url: git@github.com:acme/my-project.git
repo name: my-project
managed repo path: ~/.outpost/repos/github.com/acme/my-project.git
action: cloned
registry action: created
ready: true</span>

<span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost create --ticket PROJ-123 --type feat --repo my-project
<span class="terminal-output">outpost create
ticket: PROJ-123
branch: feat/PROJ-123
workspace directory: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123</span>

<span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost workspace list
<span class="terminal-output">outpost workspace list
workspaces: 1
- PROJ-123 [ready]
  workspace directory: ~/.outpost/worktrees/PROJ-123
  type: feat
  branch: feat/PROJ-123</span>

<span class="terminal-prompt">$ </span>outpost workspace remove PROJ-123
<span class="terminal-output">outpost workspace remove
ticket: PROJ-123
status: success</span></pre>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="commands" class="prose">
      <h2 id="commands">Commands</h2>
      <div class="feature-grid">
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">outpost create</code></h3>
          <p>Create branches and worktrees across repos for a ticket. Supports dry-run, --base, and interactive prompting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">outpost workspace</code></h3>
          <p>List, show, and remove workspaces. Removal checks for uncommitted changes and verifies ownership.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">outpost repo</code></h3>
          <p>Add, list, show, fetch, and remove repositories with managed bare mirrors.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">outpost doctor</code></h3>
          <p>Report environment status including config validity, repo health, and workspace state.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">outpost describe</code></h3>
          <p>Show command specifications with argument and option details. Machine-readable with --json.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature-item">
          <h3><code translate="no">--json</code> output</h3>
          <p>Supported commands expose JSON output with a stable contract including ok, data, and exitCode fields. Help and version output stay plain text.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="links" class="prose">
      <h2 id="links">Links</h2>
      <ul class="link-list">
        <li><a href="https://github.com/abijith-suresh/outpost">Source on GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@abijith-suresh/outpost">Package on npm</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--space-s);">
        Outpost is pre-v1. Commands and output contracts may change between releases.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
